HEADWORD: Diaspore
<hw>Di"a*spore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Gr. <?/ a
scattering; <grk>dia`</grk> through, asunder + <?/ to sow, scatter like
seed: cf. F. <ets>diaspore</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
hydrate of alumina, often occurring in white lamellar masses with
brilliant pearly luster; -- so named on account of its decrepitating
when heated before the blowpipe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

